---
import UseCase from '../../../UseCase.astro';
import UseCaseInteractive from '../../../UseCaseInteractive.astro';
import Usage from '../../../Usage.astro';
import UsageItem from '../../../UsageItem.astro';
---

<UseCase
  title="Clarify Scope and Capabilities"
  description="State clearly what the AI can and can't do, and for whom or in what contextâ€”so users don't assume it handles everything or works in every situation."
>
  <UseCaseInteractive clsHeight={112} label="Scope and capabilities" toggle>
    <div class="grid gap-600 w-full">
      <div class="grid gap-400 p-600 rounded-lg bg-tone-neutral-09 border border-tone-neutral-03">
        <div class="grid gap-200">
          <mds-text typography="label"><b>Explicit Scope</b></mds-text>
          <mds-text typography="body"
            >This assistant helps you draft and summarize documents in English, Spanish, and French.
            It does not give legal, medical, or financial advice. For those, consult a qualified
            professional.</mds-text
          >
          <mds-text typography="caption" class="text-tone-neutral-05"
            >Users see what's in scope (languages, tasks) and what's out (advice domains).</mds-text
          >
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="grid gap-400 p-600 rounded-lg bg-tone-neutral-09 border border-tone-neutral-03">
        <div class="grid gap-200">
          <mds-text typography="label"><b>Context Where It Applies</b></mds-text>
          <mds-text typography="body"
            >Recommendations are based on your organization's policy and the data you've provided.
            They may not apply to edge cases or regions we don't yet support. [See supported
            scenarios]</mds-text
          >
          <mds-text typography="caption" class="text-tone-neutral-05"
            >Clarifies the conditions under which the AI is designed to work.</mds-text
          >
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="grid gap-400 p-600 rounded-lg bg-status-error-10 border border-status-error-03">
        <div class="grid gap-200">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-200">
            <mds-icon name="mi/outline/error" class="text-status-error-05"></mds-icon>
            <mds-text typography="label"><b>Vague or Absent Scope (Problematic)</b></mds-text>
          </div>
          <mds-text typography="body"
            >"AI-powered assistant" or "Smart suggestions" with no description of what it does,
            which languages or domains it supports, or what it doesn't do. Users assume it can
            handle anything.</mds-text
          >
          <mds-text typography="caption" class="text-status-error-06"
            >Leads to misuse in unsupported contexts and disappointment when the system fails
            outside its scope.</mds-text
          >
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </UseCaseInteractive>
  <Usage>
    <UsageItem variant="do">
      Describe what the AI is designed to do, in what context (e.g. languages, domains, data), and
      what it does not do.
    </UsageItem>
    <UsageItem variant="dont">
      Use generic labels like "AI-powered" or "Smart" without stating scope or limitations.
    </UsageItem>
    <UsageItem variant="do">
      Call out high-stakes exclusions (e.g. not legal/medical/financial advice) in user-visible
      copy.
    </UsageItem>
    <UsageItem variant="dont">
      Leave scope and boundaries implicit so users infer capabilities incorrectly.
    </UsageItem>
  </Usage>
</UseCase>
